      "id": "F-001",
      "pathId": "no-dark-mode",
      "url": "http://localhost:8090/#no-dark-mode",
      "principleId": "respect-user-preferences",
      "principleCheckId": "respects-color-scheme",
      "guidanceId": "dark-mode",
      "guidanceCategory": "user-experience",
      "severity": "high",
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Surface ignores prefers-color-scheme: dark and stays a light card.",
      "evidence": "Under emulated prefers-color-scheme: dark, a computed-style probe and a clipped screenshot of .ndm-card show background rgb(255, 255, 255) (a glaring white surface). The card hard-codes background: #ffffff; color: #111111 with no light-dark() and no per-element color-scheme. Re-tinting fails purely because the adaptation is missing.",
      "suggestedFix": "Declare color-scheme: light dark on the card (or root) and use light-dark(#ffffff, #1e1e1e) for surfaces and light-dark(#111111, #eeeeee) for text so the card follows the user preference. See Modern Web Guidance id dark-mode.",
      "effort": "small",
      "scenario": "no-dark-mode",
      "artifacts": [
        "evidence/no-dark-mode-dark.png"
      ]
