      "evidence": "Lighthouse (accessibility 91) flagged color-contrast: score 0 on the three .pf-btn buttons; axe-core, injected from CDN via the evaluate primitive and run in-page, independently reported one serious color-contrast violation across 3 nodes. The grey #f2f2f2 button background with the default text does not meet the contrast threshold. This was not one of the playground's six explicitly seeded CSS scenarios; the agentic audit surfaced it from the Lighthouse-dimension principles.",
      "suggestedFix": "Raise the button text/background contrast to at least 4.5:1 for body text (e.g. darken the label or the border, or use a higher-contrast surface). Verify with axe / Lighthouse after the change.",
